description:
It's a new video about Dysprosium, a metal named after its own elusiveness. More links and info in full description ↓↓↓

Support us on Patreon: https://www.patreon.com/periodicvideos
Here's the latest version our table of patrons: http://periodicvideos.com/patreon_table/table.jpg

This video features Professor Sir Martyn Poliakoff and senior technician Neil Barnes at the University of Nottingham's School of Chemistry.

Videos on all 118 elements: http://bit.ly/118elements

PAPERS FROM THE VIDEO
Magnetic hysteresis up to 80 kelvin in a dysprosium metallocene single-molecule magnet - https://www.science.org/doi/10.1126/science.aav0652
Soft magnetic hysteresis in a dysprosium amide–alkene complex up to 100 kelvin - https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-025-09138-0

From the School of Chemistry at The University of Nottingham: http://bit.ly/NottChem
